# Core rules (SOA Exam P study app, Anki fork)

Read `AGENTS.md`, `PRD.md`, and `SPEC_CHECKLIST.md` before coding. Rubric wins on conflicts.

- ALWAYS make real changes in Anki's **Rust engine** for scheduling/backend work. NEVER reimplement the scheduler in JS/Swift/Python: doing so caps the grade at 50%.
- The app has **three separate scores** (memory, performance, readiness), each shown **with a range**. NEVER blend them into one number.
- NEVER show a readiness number without the honesty bundle: evidence, missing data, past accuracy, a range, and the single best next action.
- The **give-up rule is code**: return NO score below the stated data threshold. It is an assertion + a test, not a UI hint.
- NEVER let test items leak into training. NEVER emit an AI output without a named source. These are automatic fails / zeros.
- Both apps MUST still produce a score with **AI switched off**.
- Do NOT add AI (model calls, generated cards, chatbot) until the Wednesday core is complete.
- Work one deadline at a time; plan and name files before editing; after each change verify tests pass, undo works, and the collection is not corrupted. Then update `SPEC_CHECKLIST.md`.
